  "metadata": {"spec-version": "1.5"},
  "configuration-groups": [
    {
      "label": "Basic",
      "properties": [
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "gcpProjectId",
          "label": "Project ID",
          "widget-attributes": {"default": "auto-detect"}
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",

        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "guid",
          "label": "GUID",
          "widget-attributes": {"placeholder": "Ex. : 42010A8400281EEC82FF11F2732D73D3"}
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "massTransferId",
          "label": "Mass Transfer ID",
          "widget-attributes": {"placeholder": "Ex. : 00R"}
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "SLT Configuration",
      "properties": [
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "sapJcoLibGcsPath",
          "label": "SAP JCo Library GCS Path",
          "widget-attributes": {"placeholder": "Google Cloud Storage path having SAP JCo libraries. Ex: gs://cdf-sap-dependent-files/v3_0_20"}
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "jco.client.ashost",
          "label": "SAP Server Host",
          "widget-attributes": {"placeholder": "SAP Application Server (AS) Hostname or IP (Ex. : 10.132.0.40)"}
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "jco.client.sysnr",
          "label": "SAP System Number",
          "widget-attributes": {"placeholder": "Ex: 00"}

        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "jco.client.client",
          "label": "SAP Client",
          "widget-attributes": {
            "max-length": 3,
            "placeholder": "Ex: 100"
          }
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "jco.client.lang",
          "label": "SAP Language",
          "widget-attributes": {
            "default": "EN",
            "placeholder": "Ex: DE, EN, JP etc."
          }
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "textbox",
          "name": "jco.client.user",
          "label": "SAP Logon Username",
          "widget-attributes": {"placeholder": "Ex. : cdfsltdev"}
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "password",
          "name": "jco.client.passwd",
          "label": "SAP Logon Password"
        },
        {
          "widget-type": "toggle",
          "name": "suspendSltJob",
          "label": "Suspend SLT replication when replication job stops",
          "widget-attributes": {
            "default": "false",
            "off": {
              "label": "No",
              "value": "false"
            },
            "on": {
              "label": "Yes",
              "value": "true"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "replicateExistingData",
          "widget-type": "toggle",
          "label": "Replicate Existing Data",
          "widget-attributes": {
            "default": "true",
            "off": {
              "label": "No",
              "value": "false"
            },
            "on": {
              "label": "Yes",
              "value": "true"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "GCP Credentials",
      "properties": [{
        "name": "serviceAccountKey",
        "widget-type": "securekey-textarea",
        "label": "Service Account Key",
        "widget-attributes": {"default": "auto-detect"}
      }]
    }
  ],

# SAP SLT CDC Source plugin
## Description
SAP SLT Replication Source plugin enables real time migration of data from SAP SLT server to the configured 
target in the replication job.

## Properties
You can configure the following properties for the SAP SLT.

**Note**: The following indicators are used to define the fields:  
**M** - Indicates Macros are supported for the respective field  
**O** - Optional field

**Project ID:** Google Cloud Project ID, which uniquely identifies a project. It can be found on the Dashboard 
in the Google Cloud Platform Console. Default: auto-detect  
**Data Replication GCS Path**: The Google Cloud Storage path which contains data for replication. 
This path must be the same which is configured in SAP SLT jobs.
The provided path internally will be concatenated with 'Mass Transfer Id' followed by 'Source Table Name'.   
Format: gs://<base-path>/<mass-transfer-id>/<source-table-name>  
Example: gs://slt_bucket/012/MARA   
**GUID**: SLT GUID - a unique identifier, assigned to SAP SLT mass transfer id.  
**Mass Transfer ID**: SLT Mass Transfer ID - a unique identifier, assigned to configuration in SAP SLT.

## SLT Configuration

**SAP JCo Library GCS Path**: The Google Cloud Storage path which contains the user uploaded SAP JCo library files.
SAP JCo libraries can be downloaded from SAP Support Portal. [**Refer**](https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/how-to) 
to upload the files to GCS.     
**SAP Server Host**: SAP Application Server Hostname or IP.  
**SAP System Number**: SAP System Number.  
**SAP Client**: The SAP client to use (e.g. 100).  
**SAP Language**: SAP logon language (e.g. EN).  
**SAP Logon Username**: SAP Logon user ID.  
**SAP Logon Password (M)**: SAP Logon password for user authentication. **Recommended**: Use
[**secure macros**](
https://cdap.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DOCS/pages/801767425/Using+Secure+Keys)
for sensitive values like **User password**.  
**Suspend SLT replication when replication job stops**: Attempt to suspend the SAP SLT replication job (for the tables involved)
when the Cloud Data Fusion replication job is stopped. May not be able to honor the request if the CDF job is aborted unexpectedly.

## GCP Credentials

**Service Account Key**: Service account key to use when interacting with GCS. The service account 
must have permission to write to GCS. When running on a Google Cloud VM, this can be set to 
'auto-detect', which will use the service account key on the VM.
